  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Byte
    The Byte class stores byte addressable memory in binary, and hex
    Cpu
    Cpu class manages the fetch and execute cycle and everything necessary for managing that correctly ie.
    Gui
    The gui class gives a frame for the simulator to be visualized.
    Instruction
    The Instruction class contains representations of assembly commands.
    InstructionSet
    The InstructionSet class manages all instructions and is used for checking strings for any assembly commands and executes them if found.
    Main  
    Memory
    Memory contains all the methods and structures to simulate computer memory.
    Operator
    The operator class is the calculator and execute manager of the project.
    Register
    Registers are the non memory storage medium that the Cpu has available for working.
    Translator
    Controls the parsing of the memory image and writing to files.
